title: [SOLVED] 820-00165 Shuts down at about 20% of progress bar. Was working fine.
message: Any idea where to start with this? It happens only when booting. So it's loading something and shutting down at that same point each time. Was working for about 2 months. Onboard Apple diagnostic says there's nothing wrong. Not sure where to go with this. It was a spill. Unfortunately, no pictures and no signs of where the damage is.

title: [SOLVED] 820-00165 Shuts down at about 20% of progress bar. Was working fine.
message: Usually corrosion around CPU Vcore regulators. U1950 pin 8?

title: [SOLVED] 820-00165 Shuts down at about 20% of progress bar. Was working fine.
message: You nailed this one. C7319 was beat up and barely making a connection. It worked for a while then failed. I replaced it along with a couple other ugly capacitors around it and it's back up and running. Thanks.

title: [SOLVED] 820-00165 Shuts down at about 20% of progress bar. Was working fine.
message: The board would work fine without C7319, just a bypass cap among many others. So the board working again is something else...

title: [SOLVED] 820-00165 Shuts down at about 20% of progress bar. Was working fine.
message: Ok, good to know. Maybe one of the capacitors around it then. Not sure. It was solidly not working until I replaced those 4 capacitors and now it is solidly working. Hopefully it holds up.
